<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>In this case, the composed function is one of the given,  
$$
\begin{align*}
	f(g(x)) &amp;= x
\end{align*}
$$

Start with $f(x)$

$$
\begin{align*}
	f(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x+1} \\
	f(g(x)) &amp;= \frac{2}{ g(x) +1}
\end{align*}
$$

Since $f(g(x))=x$,

$$
\begin{align*}
	\frac{2}{ g(x) +1} &amp;= x \\
	g(x) +1 &amp;= \frac{2}{x} \\
	g(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x} -1		\tag*{(ans.)}
\end{align*}
$$

You can check your answer by composing the function,

$$
\begin{align*}
	f(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x+1} \\
	f(g(x)) &amp;= 	\frac{2}{\br{ \frac{2}{x} -1 }+1} \\
	&amp;= \frac{2}{\frac{2}{x}} \\
	&amp;= x
\end{align*}
$$
</code></pre></div></div>

